        "content": "<p>I've opened <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/compiler-team/issues/760\">https://github.com/rust-lang/compiler-team/issues/760</a> as a proposal for upstream rust-lang/rust to enable the addition of <code>wasm32-wasip2</code> with <code>rustup target add</code>. Wanted to link that here in case anyone has thoughts/opinions! The official place for discussion is <a href=\"https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/233931-t-compiler.2Fmajor-changes/topic/Promote.20wasm32-wasip2.20to.20a.20Tier.202.20target.20compiler-team.23760/near/444568005\">on the rust-lang/rust zulip</a> but happy to chat here too</p>\n<div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/compiler-team/issues/760\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://uploads.zulipusercontent.&quot;)\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/compiler-team/issues/760\" title=\"Promote wasm32-wasip2 to a Tier 2 target · Issue #760 · rust-lang/compiler-team\">Promote wasm32-wasip2 to a Tier 2 target · Issue #760 · rust-lang/compiler-team</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">Proposal This is a proposal to upgrade the wasm32-wasip2 target, (introduced here, and implemented here), to tier 2. Currently this is a tier 3 target that requires -Zbuild-std to work with. This t...</div></div></div><div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/233931-t-compiler.2Fmajor-changes/topic/Promote.20wasm32-wasip2.20to.20a.20Tier.202.20target.20compiler-team.23760/near/444568005\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://uploads.zulipusercontent.net/b470a6a9a9c7305c1cb5dfd01f6a6cac651c1674/68747470733a2f2f7a756c69702d617661746172732e73332e616d617a6f6e6177732e636f6d2f343731352f7265616c6d2f69636f6e2e706e673f76657273696f6e3d32&quot;)\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_description\">If this message does not go away, try reloading the page.</div></div></div>",
